(72140, 138238, 0, 1, 'In Her Sea - Part of Me', '', '2014-03-05 00:00:00', 2000, 32, 0, 7, 'Since the day you left me home,\nI’ve been fighting all alone running from this mess. \nAfter all we are not the same, no,\nyou hurt me with the line you broke,\nscattered on the wall.\n\nWithout me,\nYeah, you choose a better sky to soar, to the land of dream. I say,\nYeah, I’ve never felt this way before, losing part of me.\n\nMaybe I should keep your cloths,\npretending that you’re in the room standing on the floor. \nAnd the roses you planted before,\nthey stop growing as they know the world is an empty shell.\n\nWithout me,\nYeah, you choose a better sky to soar, to the land of dream. I say,\nYeah, I’ve never felt this way before, losing part of me.\n\n‘Cause I’m trying so hard to back to what we are, \nbut you keep on walking and never turn you head.\n\nYeah, you choose a better sky to soar, to the land of dream. I say,\nYeah, I’ve never felt this way before, losing part of me.', '', 273, '', '', '', '', '她的海', '', 0, 1, 0, '2014-02-09 13:46:35', '2015-03-12 14:05:03', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
